Mike,

Go ahead and log the bug against Eclipse, if you please, since
Eclipse&#39;s mechanism for running single tests is involved (although I&#39;m
not convinced they won&#39;t bounce it to us.  :-)

That said, I wonder if part of the issue is that you&#39;re running a
JUnit 3 test class in JUnit 4.  This is of course allowed and
encouraged, but if you&#39;re not using the JUnit 4 functionality, running
the test case in JUnit 3 might be a good temporary workaround for the
situation.  Thanks,

   David Saff

